BHS Class of 2020:
We look forward to seeing you for your scheduled appointment next Monday and Tuesday (4/27 and 4/28).
As you leave the school, we ask that you stop and sign the BHS 2020 Seniors #Quarantined sign. It is displayed near the oak tree by the faculty parking lot. As you sign, please consider the amount of signatures and room needed on the board for all to be included. This will forever be displayed on our campus in your honor and in appreciation of your resilience, understanding, and determination during this unprecedented time.

National Read Across America Day was celebrated today in the BHS Library in honor of Dr. Seuss. Special bookmarks and other Seuss related items were given as students checked out books throughout the day.
The Butter Battle Book, a story of tolerance and acceptance, was read by librarian Mrs. Amy Adams to students from Mrs. Karla Mizell’s seventh grade class. They then discussed the themes of the book, made homemade butter, and enjoyed cupcakes in honor and appreciation of the joy of reading Dr. Seuss promoted through his writing.

post_text: The physical science classes of Mrs. Jones completed a project that tested the scientific concepts of speed and motion. Groups had to work together to create a container that would hold a raw egg. When the container was dropped from a high position, the intended result was for the raw egg to remain intact.

Attention BHS Parents:
Please be advised that our uniform policy will be strictly enforced this semester. This includes appropriate color collared shirt(7-8 wear gold, 9-12 wear black) khaki bottoms, and school appropriate shoes. A school ID card must also be visible at all times. New ID’s will be available for purchase for $3 the week of January 13-17. They will return to the regular price of $5 after the 17th. We look forward to a great semester!

Today, Lumberjack Cheerleader Grace Mangrum participated in the London New Year’s Day Parade. Grace was selected as an All-American Cheerleader at Varsity’s Urban Cheerleading Experience Camp last summer and invited to participate in the event. She was among over 700 cheerleaders performing during the “London Loves Life” themed parade. We are extremely proud of her for representing Bogalusa High School across the pond. #LumberjacksForever
#JacksPride #LNYDP #VarsityLondon
